## Getting Started

> **Requirements**: Unreal Engine 5.x / Visual Studio 2022 (C++ workload) / Git LFS

```bash
git clone https://github.com/<your-account>/Greystone.git
```

1. Right-click `Greystone.uproject` and select **Generate Visual Studio project files**
2. Open the generated `.sln` in Visual Studio and build with the **Development Editor** configuration
3. Open `Greystone.uproject` in Unreal Engine 5
4. Press **Play** in the editor

## Controls

| Action | Key |
| --- | --- |
| Move | `W` `A` `S` `D` |
| Look | Mouse |
| Light Attack | Left Click |
| Heavy Attack | Right Click (hold to charge) |
| Dodge (Roll) | `Space` |
| Block | `Shift` |

